did.abstract: The Kentucky Academy of Science records (dated 1892-2018, undated; 17.15 cubic feet; 20 boxes) comprise minutes, official correspondence, and scientific papers presented by members documenting this professional society of scientists and science educators.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Collection is open to researchers by appointment.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Collection is arranged into seven series by subject: Records; Membership index cards; Publications, Programs, and Awards; Documentation on Assorted Science and Academy Topics; Kentucky Junior Academy of Science Records; Presidential Records; Visual Materials. Within these series, materials are arranged chronilogically.

bioghist.head: Historical Note
bioghist.p: The Kentucky Academy of Science, officially established in 1914, is based in Lexington, Kentucky. It is an honorary and professional society of Kentucky scientists and science educators, although opportunities for membership are extended to residents of states outside Kentucky as well. Its primary objectives as an organization are to encourage scientific research and education throughout Kentucky. In order to achieve these objectives, the Kentucky Academy of Science holds an annual meeting where members can share and discuss research and interests across numerous science disciplines. It also publishes the Journal of the Kentucky Academy of Science (previously called Transactions of the Kentucky Academy of Science), which serves as both the official record of the Kentucky Academy of Science, as well as a collection of member research papers and findings. To further encourage an interest in science education and careers, the Kentucky Academy of Science sponsors the Kentucky Junior Academy of Science, an organization targeted toward pre-college students.

Sources: History of the Kentucky Academy of Science over Its First 100 Years, Journal of the Kentucky Academy of Science, vol. 75(1-2), 2014, Page 1. https://www.kyscience.org/docs/History-of-KAS-100-years1.pdf, accessed January 6, 2023.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Kentucky Academy of Science records (dated 1892-2018, undated; 17.15 cubic feet, 20 boxes) comprises minutes, official correspondence, and scientific papers presented by members documenting this professional society of scientists and science educators. There are also newsletters, financial statements, newspaper clippings, an assortment of presidential records, and documents covering a variety of scientific topics/issues of interest to the Academy. Additionally, the records of the Kentucky Junior Academy of Science are included in this collection, which is also comprised of minutes, official correspondence, and scientific papers presented by members, as well as convention registration, judging, and awards information. This collection also includes photos of numerous meetings and exhibitions of the Kentucky Academy of Science, as well as official bound publications of members' scientific papers.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: The physical rights to the materials in this collection are held by the University of Kentucky Special Collections Research Center.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Records series contains organizational correspondence (primarily regarding Academy business, membership, events, and finances), newsletters, meeting mnutes, newspaper clippings, members' scientific papers, and financial statements.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Membership index cards series contains a multitude of index cards containing member information (such as contact details and area of study) and status between 1914 and 1936. Information was kept on both active members and those who had died or resigned.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Presidential Records series contains the official correspondence and organizational documents of a select number of Academy presidents. These presidents include: Frederick Brown, Charles V. Covell, Richard R. Hannan, W.P. Hettinger, Jr., L.Y. Lancaster, J.G. Rodriguez, Ward C. Sumpter, and Joe E. Winstead.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Visual Materials series contains photographs from various meetings and convenetions of the Academy at numerous universities across Kentucky, as well as other locations. Sub-series include: Kentucky Junior Academy of Science Science Fair Photos; Experiment and Exhibit Photos; Meeting at the University of Louisville; Meeting at Morehead State University; Meeting at the Radison Plaza Hotel in Lexington, Kentucky; Meeting at Eastern Kentucky University; Meeting at the University of Kentucky; Annual Meeting of the American Association for the Advancement of Science in New Orleans, Louisiana; and Innovative Applications of Constructed Wetlands Symposium in Lexington, Kentucky. Photographs cover a range of subjects including: Academy members, speeches, exhibits, experiments, and scenery. There are also some photo negatives and slides used during a presentation at the 74th Annual Meeting in 1988.
